<MELItem itemNbr="21-22-02" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-21-22-02.1.2-21-22-02">
<Title>Flight Deck Boost Isolation Valve</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Flight deck boost isolation valve is deactivated closed.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Air conditioning packs operate normally</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Note>
<Para>For an air conditioning pack to be operating normally, certain items associated with that system must operate normally.  See MEL item 21-51-01 for a list of those items.</Para>
</Note>
<Para>Deactivate flight deck boost isolation valve closed (AMM DDG 21-22-02).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Using a flight deck multi-function display only, open the following circuit breakers and lock with an INOP tag:</Para>
<List listType="A.">
<ListItem>
<Para>BOOST SUPPLY VLV 	CLOSE-FLT DECK</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>BOOST SUPPLY VLV 	OPEN-FLT DECK</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Gain access to flight deck boost isolation valve.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Manually turn the open/close knob until the valve is fully closed.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
</DispatchItems>